  "prompt": "What\u2019s the way to get a PR in Canada?",
  "response": "There are several ways to obtain Permanent Residency (PR) in Canada:\n\n1. Express Entry System\n- Federal Skilled Worker Program\n- Federal Skilled Trades Program\n- Canadian Experience Class\n- Requires qualification based on points system\n- Factors include age, education, work experience, language skills\n\n2. Provincial Nominee Program (PNP)\n- Each province has its own immigration streams\n- Nomination based on specific labor market needs\n- Requires job offer or skills matching provincial requirements\n\n3. Family Sponsorship\n- Sponsored by spouse, partner, parent, or child who is a Canadian citizen or PR\n- Must meet specific relationship and financial requirements\n\n4. Business/Entrepreneur Immigration\n- Start-up Visa Program\n- Self-employed persons program\n- Requires investment or business experience\n\n5. Refugee and Humanitarian Immigration\n- For individuals seeking asylum or protection\n\n6. Quebec-Specific Immigration\n- Separate immigration system with unique requirements\n\n7. Atlantic Immigration Pilot Program\n- Targets skilled workers and international graduates in Atlantic provinces\n\nCommon requirements across most pathways:\n- Language proficiency (English or French)\n- Educational credentials assessment\n- Medical examination\n- Police background check\n- Sufficient financial resources\n\nEach pathway has specific eligibility criteria, documentation requirements, and application processes.",
